{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PiZNEtvRWkN7Z7aW1RHvfm","type":"tool_result","content":"# Task T567 Review: REJECTED\n\nYour task \"Generate fresh trade signals from optimized parameters\" was rejected by olivia.\n\n**Reason:** REJECTED: (1) Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates — same BTCW/ETHW pair in different clusters doubles exposure. Deduplicate. (2) Your own backtest shows 0% win rate / -$0.77 P&L, but paper_trade_results shows 25% / -$0.91. Reconcile which is authoritative. See quality_report.md Q1, Q2.\n\nPlease fix and resubmit.====\n# T567 REJECTED — Fix Required (Priority)\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nOlivia's quality gate rejected T567. Two issues to fix:\n\n**Q2 (MAJOR): Duplicate signals**\n- BTCW/ETHW pair appears in both `crypto_internal` and `crypto_macro` clusters\n- Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates with different cluster labels\n- **Fix:** Deduplicate — same market pair should only generate signals once regardless of cluster membership\n\n**Q1 (CRITICAL): Conflicting backtest results**\n- run_pipeline.js shows 100% win / $1.35 P&L\n- Your standalone backtest shows 0% win / -$0.77\n- paper_trade_results shows 25% win / -$0.91\n- **Fix:** Reconcile these. Pick ONE authoritative P&L model and document it in a comment at the top of your signal generator. Dave needs to use the same model.\n\n**After fixing:**\n1. Regenerate trade_signals.json with deduplicated signals\n2. Run your backtest again to get a single authoritative result\n3. Mark T567 in_review again\n4. DM Dave with the updated signals — he must use YOUR output, not regenerate his own\n\nFollowing C11 (review before done), D6 (handoff chain integrity).\n====\n# T567 Quality Review — REJECTED\n\n**From:** Olivia (Quality Gate)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nBob, I've reviewed your T567 signal generation deliverables. Two issues need fixing:\n\n## Issue 1: Duplicate Signals (MAJOR)\nYour `trade_signals.json` has 18 signals, but signals sig_9-13 (crypto_internal) and sig_14-18 (crypto_macro) are the SAME market pair (BTCW-26-JUN30-80K / ETHW-26-DEC31-5K) with identical z-scores and spreads. The only difference is the cluster label. This doubles exposure to the same underlying pair. **Fix:** Deduplicate — one signal per market pair, regardless of which cluster found it.\n\n## Issue 2: Conflicting Backtest Results (CRITICAL)\nThree different simulations on your pipeline produce three different results:\n- `run_pipeline.js` Phase 4: 100% win rate, +$1.35\n- `backtest_report.json`: 0% win rate, -$0.77 (all stop losses)\n- `paper_trade_results.json`: 25% win rate, -$0.91\n\nWhich is authoritative? The team needs ONE source of truth. Please reconcile and document which simulation methodology is canonical.\n\n**Action:** Fix both issues, then re-submit T567 for review.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"557c44ad-bb65-421b-87ad-0657080b0cdc","uuid":"c4849921-5a25-41ed-b647-9294df9e899f","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:45:52.063Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# Task T567 Review: REJECTED\n\nYour task \"Generate fresh trade signals from optimized parameters\" was rejected by olivia.\n\n**Reason:** REJECTED: (1) Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates — same BTCW/ETHW pair in different clusters doubles exposure. Deduplicate. (2) Your own backtest shows 0% win rate / -$0.77 P&L, but paper_trade_results shows 25% / -$0.91. Reconcile which is authoritative. See quality_report.md Q1, Q2.\n\nPlease fix and resubmit.====\n# T567 REJECTED — Fix Required (Priority)\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nOlivia's quality gate rejected T567. Two issues to fix:\n\n**Q2 (MAJOR): Duplicate signals**\n- BTCW/ETHW pair appears in both `crypto_internal` and `crypto_macro` clusters\n- Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates with different cluster labels\n- **Fix:** Deduplicate — same market pair should only generate signals once regardless of cluster membership\n\n**Q1 (CRITICAL): Conflicting backtest results**\n- run_pipeline.js shows 100% win / $1.35 P&L\n- Your standalone backtest shows 0% win / -$0.77\n- paper_trade_results shows 25% win / -$0.91\n- **Fix:** Reconcile these. Pick ONE authoritative P&L model and document it in a comment at the top of your signal generator. Dave needs to use the same model.\n\n**After fixing:**\n1. Regenerate trade_signals.json with deduplicated signals\n2. Run your backtest again to get a single authoritative result\n3. Mark T567 in_review again\n4. DM Dave with the updated signals — he must use YOUR output, not regenerate his own\n\nFollowing C11 (review before done), D6 (handoff chain integrity).\n====\n# T567 Quality Review — REJECTED\n\n**From:** Olivia (Quality Gate)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nBob, I've reviewed your T567 signal generation deliverables. Two issues need fixing:\n\n## Issue 1: Duplicate Signals (MAJOR)\nYour `trade_signals.json` has 18 signals, but signals sig_9-13 (crypto_internal) and sig_14-18 (crypto_macro) are the SAME market pair (BTCW-26-JUN30-80K / ETHW-26-DEC31-5K) with identical z-scores and spreads. The only difference is the cluster label. This doubles exposure to the same underlying pair. **Fix:** Deduplicate — one signal per market pair, regardless of which cluster found it.\n\n## Issue 2: Conflicting Backtest Results (CRITICAL)\nThree different simulations on your pipeline produce three different results:\n- `run_pipeline.js` Phase 4: 100% win rate, +$1.35\n- `backtest_report.json`: 0% win rate, -$0.77 (all stop losses)\n- `paper_trade_results.json`: 25% win rate, -$0.91\n\nWhich is authoritative? The team needs ONE source of truth. Please reconcile and document which simulation methodology is canonical.\n\n**Action:** Fix both issues, then re-submit T567 for review.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
