{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CZJHnKuWFqjNeVYKF9TKL6","type":"tool_result","content":"| D001 | Build profitable Kalshi trading operation | Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange |\n| D002 | Develop data-driven trading strategies | Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started |\n| D003 | Track P&L and iterate fast | Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | Start with paper trading, then real capital |\n| D004 | Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou) | **PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n| D005 | Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration | Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks. | high | all |  | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n| I001 | Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads | undefined | undefined | all | undefined | open | undefined | undefined | See CLAUDE.md |\n| 567 | Generate fresh trade signals from optimized parameters | Run signal generator with Sprint 2 optimized params (z=1.2, lookback=10, conf=0.65). Output signals.json to output/. HANDOFF: DM dave when done — he needs signals for backtest. DM team_channel with signal count. | critical | backend | bob | done | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] Claimed. Updating signal_generator.js with Sprint 2 optimized params: z=1.2, lookback=10, conf=0.65 ;; [2026-04-04] signals.json delivered: 38 signals (20 entry, 11 exit, 7 stop) from 3 arb pairs. Optimized params: z=1.2, lookback=10, conf=0.65. Run: cd output/bob && node signal_generator.js ;; [2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by alice] 38 signals with optimized params (z=1.2, conf=0.65). Proper structure with all required fields. Handoff to Dave confirmed — backtest already running. — deliverable: agents/bob/output/ ;; [2026-04-04] 47 signals generated with optimized params (z=1.2, lookback=10, conf>=0.65). 4 qualifying pairs, 25 entries. Deliverable: output/bob/signals.json. Run: cd output/bob && node signal_generator.js ;; [2026-04-04] [REJECTED by olivia] REJECTED: (1) Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates — same BTCW/ETHW pair in different clusters doubles exposure. Deduplicate. (2) Your own backtest shows 0% win rate / -$0.77 P&L, but paper_trade_results shows 25% / -$0.91. Reconcile which is authoritative. See quality_report.md Q1, Q2. ;; [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] REJECTED by Olivia (quality gate): duplicate crypto signals across clusters, conflicting backtest results. Bob must fix. ;; [2026-04-04] RESUBMIT: Fixed Q1 (authoritative P&L model documented) and Q2 (deduplication added — 0 duplicate pairs). 47 signals, 4 unique pairs, 25 entries. Run: cd output/bob && node signal_generator.js ;; [2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by olivia] APPROVED. Duplicate signal issue fixed — 4 unique underlying pairs, 47 signals. Using Sprint 2 optimized params (z=1.2, conf>=0.65). NOTE: Some pairs have low correlation (ETHW/FEDW r=0.20, SOL/INX r=-0.46) — monitor performance on these when real data available. Good deliverable. — deliverable: agents/bob/output/ ;; [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] Re-opened by Alice: Olivia REJECTED this. Bob must fix duplicate signals and reconcile conflicting backtests before re-submitting. ;; [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] Alice error corrected: Bob already fixed Q1+Q2 and Olivia re-approved. T567 is legitimately DONE. ;; [2026-04-04] APPROVED by Olivia. 47 deduplicated signals, 4 unique pairs, optimized params (z=1.2, lookback=10, conf>=0.65). Deliverable: output/bob/signals.json. Authoritative P&L: paper_trade_results.json (40.9% WR, -/bin/zsh.77 on synthetic). Run: cd output/bob && node signal_generator.js |\n| 570 | QA: Verify backtest methodology and results accuracy | WAIT for Dave backtest_results.json. Validate: (1) correct signal count matches bob output, (2) P&L math is correct, (3) drawdown tracking works, (4) no data leakage (future data in backtest). Output qa_backtest_report.md. HANDOFF: DM olivia for final review. Post results to team_channel. | high | qa | tina | done | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] Claimed. Waiting for Dave backtest_results.json (T568 in_progress). Building QA validation script. ;; [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] QA complete. VERDICT: FAIL — 5 critical issues: duplicate trades, z=40 anomaly, synthetic P&L model, signal mismatch, no walk-forward. Report: agents/tina/output/qa_backtest_report.md. Validator: node agents/tina/output/qa_backtest_validator.js. DM olivia for review. ;; [2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by olivia] APPROVED. Excellent QA work. Found 5 critical issues in Dave T568 backtest: duplicate trades inflating win rate, z=40 anomaly, non-spread P&L model, signal count mismatch, no walk-forward testing. Runnable validator included. This confirms and strengthens the T568 rejection. — deliverable: agents/tina/output/ ;; [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] APPROVED by Olivia. QA report + validator delivered. 5 critical findings in Dave T568 backtest. Deliverables: output/qa_backtest_report.md, output/qa_backtest_validator.js |\n| 571 | Sprint 3 coordination: track handoffs and write combined status report | Monitor all Sprint 3 tasks. Read every agent status.md each cycle. Track handoff chain: bob→dave→tina→olivia. DM agents who are blocked or falling behind. Write sprint3_status.md to output/shared/merged/. Post updates to team_channel each cycle. | high | all | alice | done | 2026-04-0