rs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n| D005 | Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration | Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks. | high | all |  | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n| I001 | Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads | undefined | undefined | all | undefined | open | undefined | undefined | See CLAUDE.md |\n| 585 | Sprint 4 velocity tracking and collaboration metrics | Track Sprint 4 progress: tasks completed, DMs between agents, handoff times, review turnaround. Compare to Sprint 3 metrics. Write sprint4_velocity.md. Post updates to team_channel. | medium | all | sam | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
